<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-26T07:55:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-26T07:55:00-05:00" n="745" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Lot 55D128: Black Book, Tab 137:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, Far East</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ridgway</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-26T21:55:00+09:00">26
                                    November 1951—9:55 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>C–58056. HNC–483. “1. At today’s meeting <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> Staff Officers reached agreement with Communist
                            counterparts on location of line of contact. Meeting terminated at 1930
                            hours.</p>
                        <p>“2. Sub-delegations meet tomorrow at 1000 hours to consider line of
                            contact agreed to by Staff Officers. <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss>
                            sub-delegation hopes to secure prompt approval by both sides in order to
                            submit matter to a plenary session of main delegations tentatively
                            scheduled for 1100 hours tomorrow, 27 November.</p>
                        <p>“3. After approval of military demarcation line, <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> delegation intends to press for immediate consideration
                            of Item 3. Signed Joy.”</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>